    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "I had this problem recently, running <code>flutter doctor --verbose</code> it will show you lots of details.  For example, what dependencies you might be missing or where it&#39;s looking for java runtimes.    The problem for me ended up being the fact that flutter requires android studio(AS) to be installed even though I&#39;m using intellij, and when you install AS it packages its own JRE.  Try updating your AS or AS&#39;s bundled JRE"
