    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1200759,
      "reputation" : 798,
      "user_id" : 1171479,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/6NxQ9.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Jan Seevers",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1171479/jan-seevers"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1661249796,
    "creation_date" : 1661249796,
    "answer_id" : 73456924,
    "question_id" : 58125830,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I got the problem after an upgrade to java 17. Then I was running the older Run/Debug configuration and needed to update the path to the JDK</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KKMjP.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KKMjP.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 397698,
      "reputation" : 344,
      "user_id" : 761977,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0725179d86dd2a550c1d5fc42a01ca8a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Sergey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/761977/sergey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1668181987,
    "creation_date" : 1668181987,
    "answer_id" : 74405037,
    "question_id" : 58125830,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this problem with Android Studio.<br />\nI fixed it by updating Gradle to 6.5, and Gradle plugin to 4.11.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 17247971,
      "reputation" : 425,
      "user_id" : 12488738,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/2993907003970721/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Qadir Khan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12488738/qadir-khan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1716396880,
    "creation_date" : 1716396880,
    "answer_id" : 78519003,
    "question_id" : 58125830,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In case of android studio, I fixed this issue by simply updated the Gradle Jdk.</p>\n<p><strong>1:</strong> At left side of android studio click on Gradle tab --&gt; next click on setting icon --&gt; select Gradle settings</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4wgFcXLj.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4wgFcXLj.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>2:</strong> Now you will see the Gradle JDK and here you can update it and it will solve the problem in my case I updated to Jbr-17</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/3aDt44lD.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/3aDt44lD.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 146433,
      "reputation" : 52702,
      "user_id" : 356895,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 66,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/022ac4ee5fc9f2474d60c9a1a6dd16f5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "JJD",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/356895/jjd"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1729173064,
    "creation_date" : 1729173064,
    "answer_id" : 79098404,
    "question_id" : 58125830,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you try to run a <code>main()</code> function in IntelliJ / Android Studio and get the following error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>/usr/lib/jvm/java-11-openjdk-amd64/bin/java ... Error: LinkageError\noccurred while loading main class ExampleKt\njava.lang.UnsupportedClassVersionError: ExampleKt has been compiled\nby a more recent version of the Java Runtime (class file version\n61.0), this version of the Java Runtime only recognizes class file versions up to 55.0</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then manually change the <code>JRE</code> version in the associated the <strong>run configuration</strong>. Select <code>Edit Configurations...</code> from the dropdown menu on top of your IDE next to the green run button.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/7oYPhw5e.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/7oYPhw5e.png\" alt=\"JRE setting\" /></a></p>\n<p>You can ease your life if you set the JRE version in the <code>Edit configuration templates...</code> so it will be applied to all future run configurations that you create.</p>\n<h1>Related</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WI-44060\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WI-44060</a></li>\n</ul>\n"
  } ],
  "owner" : {
    "account_id" : 16776598,
    "reputation" : 2017,
    "user_id" : 12127749,
    "user_type" : "registered",
    "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c8832db581573b62723f554aa0976f5c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
